ParamUsageRestriction - Enum in EasyOverrider
This enum dictates which ParamUsage values are available for use.
It is here so that using the unsafe ones requires effort and thought before being used.
The default value is ParamUsageRestriction.SAFE_ONLY, but if, for some reason, you decided that you want the __UNSAFE values, you can use ParamUsageRestriction.ALLOW_UNSAFE.

R

RecursionPreventingToString - Interface in EasyOverrider
Interface to implement when you have a possibly recursive toString() method.
This interface defines two methods: toString(Map) - must be implemented primaryToString() - only needs to be implemented if your ParamList contains primary parameters.
requireNonNull(Object, int, String, String) - Static method in class EasyOverrider.EasyOverriderUtils
Method used to make sure provided arguments aren't null.
If the provided obj is null, an IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
The message of the exception is in the format of "Argument {position} ({paramName}) provided to {methodName} cannot be null."
runSetterIfNotNull(O, BiConsumer<O, V>, V) - Static method in class EasyOverrider.EasyOverriderUtils
